Hey @mabdullahadeel, thanks for the PR!

Some notes:

- [ ] we'll want to factor out and reuse some (most?) of the logic in `pasteFromClipboard` for this. In other words, pasting and drag&dropping text on canvas should behave the same as much as it makes sense.
- [ ] let's detect whether the text is a url, and auto-linkify it (= add a `link` property on the text element). We can use a simple regex, but if you want to get fancy, this is what I've used in the past:
    
    ```js
    const rs_url_origin =
      // protocol identifier
      "(?:(?:(?:https?|ftp)://)|www\.)" +
      // host name
      "(?:(?:[a-z\\u00a1-\\uffff0-9]-?)*[a-z\\u00a1-\\uffff0-9]+)" +
      // domain name
      "(?:\\.(?:[a-z\\u00a1-\\uffff0-9]-?)*[a-z\\u00a1-\\uffff0-9]+)*" +
      // TLD identifier
      "(?:\\.(?:[a-z\\u00a1-\\uffff]{2,}))";
    
    const rs_url_resourcePath = "(?:[/?#]\\\S*)?";
    
    const re_url = new RegExp(`^${rs_url_origin}${rs_url_resourcePath}$`, "i");
    ```

